WEBVTT

00:07.000 --> 00:08.750
HEY!

00:08.750 --> 00:10.125
JUST CAUGHT US
SOME DINNER.

00:10.125 --> 00:11.834
AH, SEAFOOD.

00:11.834 --> 00:14.125
GREAT CHANGE OF PACE,
PACE.

00:14.125 --> 00:17.959
WAS THAT A NOTE OF DISGUST
I DETECTED AT OUR SUSTENANCE
OF THE OCEAN BORN?

00:17.959 --> 00:19.375
AFTER THIS TRIP, IF I
NEVER EAT ANOTHER THING

00:19.375 --> 00:23.625
THAT BREATHES THROUGH GILLS
AGAIN, IT'LL BE TOO SOON.

00:25.708 --> 00:27.458
SO THERE SHE BLOWS, HUH?

00:27.458 --> 00:30.542
CAPESIDE, MASS.
OUR FIRST AND LAST
PORT OF CALL.

00:30.542 --> 00:34.125
DOESN'T LOOK MUCH DIFFERENT
THAN WHEN WE LEFT IT,
DOES IT?

00:34.125 --> 00:36.125
THAT'S 'CAUSE
IT AIN'T, FRAULEIN.

00:38.417 --> 00:41.000
I'M IN NO MORE OF A RACE
THAN YOU ARE TO GET BACK THERE,

00:41.000 --> 00:43.417
BUT IT'S NOT LIKE WE HAVE
ANOTHER CHOICE IN THE MATTER.

00:43.417 --> 00:45.542
WE DON'T HAVE TO GO HOME.

00:45.542 --> 00:47.708
WE SURVIVED FOR 3 MONTHS
TAKING ODD JOBS.

00:47.708 --> 00:49.125
WE CAN SURVIVE
FOR AS LONG AS WE WANT.

00:49.125 --> 00:51.375
AS LONG AS WE'RE HAPPY.

00:54.166 --> 00:58.000
PACEY, IF YOU'RE SO SERIOUS
ABOUT THIS, THEN WHY
BRING THIS UP NOW...

00:58.000 --> 00:58.875
2 HOURS FROM HOME?

00:58.875 --> 01:00.333
12 HOURS FROM HOME.

01:00.333 --> 01:04.708
SEE, I THINK
WE SHOULD PROBABLY
DROP ANCHOR HERE,

01:04.708 --> 01:06.417
HAVE A BITE TO EAT,
AND THEN WE CAN DEBATE

01:06.417 --> 01:08.792
WHETHER OR NOT TO SCRAP
THIS WHOLE MISSION HOME.

01:11.875 --> 01:15.458
NO. I DON'T BELIEVE YOU,
PACEY WITTER.

01:15.458 --> 01:17.834
I MEAN, AS TRUANT AS
YOUR NATURAL INSTINCTS
MAY BE,

01:17.834 --> 01:20.959
YOU'D NEVER REALLY
SUGGEST US SKIPPING OUR
SENIOR YEAR ENTIRELY.

01:20.959 --> 01:24.583
JUST WHAT WOULD WE BE MISSING
FROM THE LAND OF POORLY
SCRIPTED MELODRAMAS, HUH?

01:24.583 --> 01:26.667
RECYCLED PLOT LINES,
TIRESOME SELF-REALIZATIONS?

01:26.667 --> 01:30.250
YOU THROW IN
THE OCCASIONAL DOWNWARD
SPIRAL OF A DEAR FRIEND

01:30.250 --> 01:32.500
AND MAYBE A BABY HERE
AND A DEATH THERE,

01:32.500 --> 01:36.917
AND ALL YOU'VE REALLY GOT IS
A RECIPE FOR SOME SOUL-SUCKING,
MIND-NUMBING ENNUI.

01:36.917 --> 01:40.250
AND I, FOR ONE, CAN SKIP IT.

01:40.250 --> 01:42.917
YOU KNOW WHAT CONTINUALLY
AMAZES ME, PACE?

01:42.917 --> 01:45.291
AND WHAT IS THAT?

01:45.291 --> 01:48.583
HOW LONG YOU'VE LASTED
WITHOUT BEING THROWN
OFF THIS BOAT.

01:48.583 --> 01:50.250
OH, FINALLY.

01:50.250 --> 01:52.417
THAT'S SOMETHING
WE CAN BOTH AGREE UPON.

02:55.792 --> 02:58.208
I'D KICK OFF JACK.

02:58.208 --> 02:59.500
[LAUGHS]

02:59.500 --> 03:02.125
YOU'D KICK ME OFF THE ISLAND
BEFORE YOU'D KICK OFF ANDIE?

03:02.125 --> 03:03.166
ANDIE'S VERY RESOURCEFUL.

03:03.166 --> 03:05.083
ALL RIGHT. GIVE IT UP
FOR GIRL POWER.

03:05.083 --> 03:06.834
YEAH. RUTHLESS ALLIANCE.

03:06.834 --> 03:08.250
OH, COME ON, JACK.

03:08.250 --> 03:10.166
IT'S NOT LIKE WE
KICKED YOU OFF FIRST
OR ANYTHING.

03:10.166 --> 03:11.708
I MEAN, WE ALREADY
KICKED OFF GRAMS.

03:11.708 --> 03:13.000
YEAH.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.583
WELL, THAT COMPARISON
JUST BATHES ME IN RELIEF.

03:15.583 --> 03:17.333
YOU GUYS SHOULD GO IN.
THE WATER'S WARM.

03:17.333 --> 03:21.125
YEAH, RIGHT. AND REAPPLY
THE 20 MINUTES OF LOTION
I JUST PUT ON.

03:21.125 --> 03:22.667
NO, THANKS.

03:22.667 --> 03:23.667
WE GOTTA GO.

03:23.667 --> 03:25.875
WE GOTTA PAINT
MRS. HAMMACOTT AT 2:00.

03:25.875 --> 03:28.667
MM, SOUNDS KINKY.

03:28.667 --> 03:30.041
HE MEANS HER HOUSE.

03:30.041 --> 03:31.250
IT'S OUR LAST ONE
THIS SEASON.

03:31.250 --> 03:32.375
AND WE STILL HAVE AN HOUR
BEFORE WE HAVE TO BE THERE.

03:32.375 --> 03:34.792
YEAH, BUT WE GOTTA STOP
BY THE HARDWARE STORE.

03:34.792 --> 03:37.417
WE GOTTA GET PAINT.
WE GOTTA GET
SOME ROLLERS.

03:37.417 --> 03:38.208
ALL RIGHT, WELL, HOLD ON.
IT'S OUR LAST BEACH DAY
OF THE SEASON.

03:38.208 --> 03:40.250
I WANT TO GET THIS ON RECORD.

03:40.250 --> 03:43.125
DAWSON, PLEASE.
NO PICTURES. I LOOK AWFUL.

03:43.125 --> 03:45.291
WELL, NOW YOU'LL LOOK AWFUL
FOR POSTERITY. READY?

03:45.291 --> 03:48.375
1...2...3.

03:48.375 --> 03:50.125
OH! NICE.

03:50.125 --> 03:51.542
WELL, SEE YOU GUYS
AT THE DIVE-IN TONIGHT.

03:51.542 --> 03:54.625
YEP. DAWSON, I HEAR
THEY'RE PLAYING JAWS.

03:54.625 --> 03:55.917
OH! GOOD.
NEVER SEEN THAT ONE YET.

03:55.917 --> 03:56.875
[ALL LAUGH]

03:56.875 --> 03:57.875
SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

03:57.875 --> 03:59.792
SEE YA.
BYE.

04:02.041 --> 04:04.708
OOH!

04:04.708 --> 04:07.417
CUTE BOYS,
2 O'CLOCK.

04:08.875 --> 04:10.166
LIKE IT EVEN MATTERS.

04:10.166 --> 04:13.542
COME ON.
ONE OF US IS SINGLE.

04:13.542 --> 04:14.500
IN THEORY.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.208
BUT IN PRACTICE, ANDIE,
LET'S FACE IT.

04:16.208 --> 04:20.041
YOUR SEX LIFE THIS SUMMER
HAS BEEN AN EPISODE
OF ABSTINENCE IN THE CITY.

04:20.041 --> 04:21.916
WELL, IS IT MY FAULT
IF THIS ONE-HORSE HAMLET

04:21.916 --> 04:24.083
HASN'T OFFERED
A SUITABLE SUMMER FLING?

04:24.083 --> 04:25.542
OH, ANDIE,
THERE ARE PLENTY OF GUYS.

04:25.542 --> 04:27.291
FACE IT. YOU'RE JUST NOT
BOLD ENOUGH TO GO UP
AND TALK TO THEM.

04:27.291 --> 04:29.792
AND IF YOU WERE
IN MY SHOES, YOU WOULD.

04:29.792 --> 04:31.333
YES!

04:31.333 --> 04:33.542
I MEAN, COME ON, I THINK THAT
MY RESUMÃ‰ SPEAKS FOR ITSELF.

04:34.583 --> 04:36.625
FINE. I'M GONNA
GO TALK TO THEM.

04:36.625 --> 04:37.667
OK.
I AM.

04:37.667 --> 04:38.041
YOU GO!

04:38.041 --> 04:38.917
I AM!

04:38.917 --> 04:41.166
WELL?

04:41.166 --> 04:44.583
WELL, I AM
JUST NEGOTIATING
THE PROPER APPROACH.

04:44.583 --> 04:48.875
WELL, EXCUSE ME WHILE I
NEGOTIATE THE PROPER APPROACH
TO THE SNACK BAR.

04:48.875 --> 04:50.375
SCAREDY-CAT.
I AM NOT.

04:50.375 --> 04:50.792
ARE SO.
AM NOT!

04:50.792 --> 04:52.792
ARE SO!

05:02.500 --> 05:05.959
BOY. THAT'S A LITTLE
ON THE HEAVY SIDE.

05:05.959 --> 05:08.083
WHO'S THAT ONE FOR?

05:08.083 --> 05:10.458
UH, MY SISTER, I THINK.
IS THAT EVERYTHING?

05:10.458 --> 05:12.291
YEAH, FOR RIGHT NOW.
I FIGURED WE'D JUST LEAVE

05:12.291 --> 05:12.875
THE REST ON THE BOAT
AND PICK IT UP TOMORROW.

05:12.875 --> 05:15.208
OK.

05:15.208 --> 05:16.417
OH...

05:16.417 --> 05:17.667
UH, BEFORE WE LEAVE,
THOUGH,

05:17.667 --> 05:19.000
THERE IS ONE OTHER THING
WE SHOULD COVER.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.125
WHAT'S THAT?

05:21.125 --> 05:22.333
WELL,
THEY'RE GONNA ASK.

05:22.333 --> 05:25.000
WHO'S GONNA
ASK WHAT?

05:25.000 --> 05:30.125
THE MASSES. THEY'RE
GONNA ASK WHAT HAPPENED
ON THE BOAT.

05:30.125 --> 05:31.708
THIS SUMMER...
BETWEEN YOU AND I...

05:31.708 --> 05:34.041
YOU KNOW...
SEXUALLY SPEAKING.

05:35.166 --> 05:37.667
NO ONE CARES, PACEY.

05:37.667 --> 05:40.417
OK, MAYBE THEY CARE,
BUT THEY'RE NOT
GONNA ASK.

05:40.417 --> 05:41.542
IT'S TOO CRASS.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.625
WE LIVE IN A CRASS AGE.

05:45.333 --> 05:46.000
OK, SO WHAT
ARE YOU GONNA SAY?

05:46.000 --> 05:48.041
THAT REALLY DEPENDS.

05:48.041 --> 05:49.333
ON?

05:49.333 --> 05:51.667
ON WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA SAY.

05:51.667 --> 05:54.125
WELL, I GUESS I'M GOING
TO SAY NOTHING BECAUSE
IT'S NO ONE'S BUSINESS.

05:54.125 --> 05:54.834
THAT'S GOOD.

05:54.834 --> 05:57.583
"NOTHING" SOUNDS PERFECT.

05:57.583 --> 05:59.542
BESIDES, THEY'RE
NOT GONNA ASK.

05:59.542 --> 06:00.583
OH, THEY'LL ASK.

06:06.583 --> 06:07.041
WELL...

06:07.041 --> 06:08.333
THIS IS IT.

06:08.333 --> 06:11.834
LAST OF OUR SUMMER,
AND...

06:11.834 --> 06:13.166
I GO LEFT, YOU GO RIGHT,

06:13.166 --> 06:15.834
AND WE SPEND
THE NEXT WHOLE 24 HOURS
AWAY FROM EACH OTHER.

06:15.834 --> 06:18.708
IF YOU'RE CURIOUS AS
TO WHY I'M NOT CURRENTLY
AWASH IN SADNESS,

06:18.708 --> 06:22.542
IT'S ONLY BECAUSE,
TO BE PERFECTLY HONEST,

06:22.542 --> 06:25.041
YOU WERE STARTIN'
TO GET ON MY NERVES, JO.

06:25.041 --> 06:26.250
OH.

06:27.208 --> 06:28.667
GOOD. WELL,
'CAUSE...YOU KNOW, I...

06:28.667 --> 06:31.875
I'D HATE TO THINK THAT
AFTER ALL OF OUR INTIMATE TALKS,

06:31.875 --> 06:34.375
YOU WERE ACTUALLY
COVERING UP YOUR ACHING HEART

06:34.375 --> 06:35.583
WITH FALSE BRAVADO.

06:35.583 --> 06:37.208
WELL, PUT YOUR MIND
AT EASE.

06:38.375 --> 06:40.125
WELL, I GUESS
I'LL CALL YOU
TOMORROW, MAYBE?

06:40.125 --> 06:42.500
OH...IF YOU THINK
ABOUT IT, SURE.

06:42.500 --> 06:43.041
OK.
GOOD LUCK OUT THERE.

06:43.041 --> 06:45.000
THANKS.

06:56.708 --> 06:59.792
EXCUSE ME.
DO YOU KNOW WHERE
THE LIGHT BULBS ARE?

06:59.792 --> 07:01.834
UH, USUALLY UP.

07:01.834 --> 07:02.959
I MEANT WHICH AISLE.

07:02.959 --> 07:04.583
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T WORK HERE.

07:04.583 --> 07:07.083
LUCKY
FOR MANAGEMENT.

07:07.083 --> 07:10.250
UM...IF IT HELPS,
I THINK THEY'RE
ON AISLE 4--

07:10.250 --> 07:11.291
GRETCHEN?

07:11.291 --> 07:13.083
DAWSON?

07:13.083 --> 07:14.000
WOW.

07:14.000 --> 07:15.000
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

07:15.000 --> 07:16.250
HI.
HI.

07:16.250 --> 07:17.250
HOW ARE YOU?

07:17.250 --> 07:18.417
I...I'M...

07:18.417 --> 07:20.458
DAMP...AT THE MOMENT.

07:21.417 --> 07:22.917
AND IN THE GRANDER
SCHEME OF THINGS?

07:22.917 --> 07:26.417
I SORT OF HEARD
THROUGH THE FAMILY
ABOUT LAST SPRING.

07:26.417 --> 07:29.500
THAT. UH...I'M FINE.

07:29.500 --> 07:31.417
I'M FINE. AND, UH,
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

07:31.417 --> 07:32.667
STILL HOME FROM COLLEGE
FOR THE SUMMER?

07:32.667 --> 07:34.333
A LITTLE BIT LONGER
THAN THAT.

07:34.333 --> 07:35.333
IT'S NO BIGGIE.
I'M JUST, UH...

07:35.333 --> 07:37.458
TAKIN'
SOME TIME OFF.

07:37.458 --> 07:41.500
OK. WELL...AT THE RISK
OF SOUNDING TRITE,

07:41.500 --> 07:43.542
IT'S...IT'S NICE
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

07:43.542 --> 07:45.542
AT THE RISK
OF SOUNDING REDUNDANT,

07:45.542 --> 07:47.166
IT'S NICE
TO SEE YOU, TOO.

07:47.166 --> 07:48.291
DAMP AND ALL.

07:48.291 --> 07:49.583
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

07:53.917 --> 07:56.375
OK. I GOT THE PAINT,
YOU GOT THE ROLLERS.

07:56.375 --> 07:57.792
WHO'S THE GIRL?

07:57.792 --> 07:59.291
UH, WHAT GIRL?

07:59.291 --> 08:01.708
THE...GIRL
YOU'RE GONNA PRETEND
TO HAVE NO KNOWLEDGE OF

08:01.708 --> 08:03.917
UNTIL I ANNOY YOU
WITH THE QUESTION

08:03.917 --> 08:05.583
OVER AND OVER
AND OVER AGAIN.

08:05.583 --> 08:07.375
THAT  GIRL. UH...

08:07.375 --> 08:08.458
LONG STORY.

08:08.458 --> 08:10.125
GOOD, 'CAUSE WE GOT
THE WHOLE NORTH SIDE

08:10.125 --> 08:11.792
OF MRS. HANCOCK'S
TO PAINT.

08:15.291 --> 08:16.750
Joey:
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU!

08:16.750 --> 08:18.333
I'M YOUR SISTER.
I'M ENTITLED TO KNOW.

08:18.333 --> 08:20.458
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

08:20.458 --> 08:21.917
I'LL REPHRASE.
I'M YOUR SISTER
WHOM YOU DITCHED

08:21.917 --> 08:23.208
HIGH AND DRY
LAST JUNE.

08:23.208 --> 08:25.166
I'M ENTITLED TO KNOW.

08:26.542 --> 08:26.792
OPEN YOUR GIFT.

08:31.166 --> 08:31.917
A PLANT.

08:31.917 --> 08:33.875
IT'S
A CAROLINA JASMINE.

08:33.875 --> 08:35.667
AT NIGHT, IF
THE WIND HIT RIGHT,

08:35.667 --> 08:37.707
WE COULD SMELL THEM
2 MILES OUT
ON THE WATER.

08:37.707 --> 08:40.667
AT NIGHT WHILE
YOU AND PACEY WERE--

08:40.667 --> 08:41.457
QUIT IT.

08:41.457 --> 08:44.333
I HAVEN'T EVEN
UNPACKED YET.

08:44.333 --> 08:46.166
OH. HEY, JOEY, WAIT.

08:49.750 --> 08:52.500
WHY IS THERE
AN UNDERWEAR-CLAD STRANGER
IN MY BEDROOM?

08:52.500 --> 08:53.708
THAT'S WHERE HE LIVES.

08:53.708 --> 08:54.542
YOU RENTED OUT MY ROOM?

08:54.542 --> 08:58.291
UNTIL TUESDAY.
COME OVER HERE.

08:58.291 --> 09:00.208
IT'S MY TURN
TO GIVE YOU A GIFT.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.000
OUR ACCOUNTING BOOK.

09:03.000 --> 09:04.417
YOU'RE SO KIND.

09:04.417 --> 09:04.667
[CHUCKLES]

09:06.625 --> 09:08.375
LOOK AT THAT NUMBER.

09:08.375 --> 09:09.875
BESSIE, I'M SORRY.

09:09.875 --> 09:12.417
I DIDN'T REALIZE HOW
DIFFICULT IT WOULD BE.

09:12.417 --> 09:15.041
JOEY,
IT HAS A PLUS NEXT
TO IT, NOT A MINUS.

09:15.041 --> 09:18.500
WELCOME TO ONE
OF THE MOST SUCCESSFUL
BED-AND-BREAKFASTS

09:18.500 --> 09:19.667
IN THE STATE, JOEY.
WE'VE DOUBLED OUR RATES,

09:19.667 --> 09:22.417
AND WE'RE STILL BOOKED
WELL THROUGH THE FALL.

09:23.500 --> 09:26.166
WELL, WHEN I CALLED,
Y-YOU NEVER MENTIONED--

09:26.166 --> 09:28.375
I WANTED IT
TO BE A SURPRISE.

09:32.500 --> 09:34.875
Andie: ...HANG OUT
WITH MY FRIENDS

09:34.875 --> 09:36.667
AND HELP MY BROTHER
WITH HIS NUMEROUS PROBLEMS.

09:36.667 --> 09:38.333
HELLO.
OH. WHY,
THERE YOU ARE,

09:38.333 --> 09:40.125
JENNIFER.
I WAS JUST

09:40.125 --> 09:41.250
CHATTING
WITH THE GUYS.

09:41.250 --> 09:44.708
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET
JEAN AND JEAN-JEAN.

09:44.708 --> 09:46.500
HMM. HELLO...JEANS.

09:46.500 --> 09:47.875
THEY'RE FRENCH.

09:47.875 --> 09:50.000
GET OUT OF DODGE.

09:50.000 --> 09:51.750
AND THEY'RE,
UH, BACKPACKING

09:51.750 --> 09:54.291
THROUGH THE EAST COAST
FOR THE SUMMER.

09:54.291 --> 09:56.500
JUST STOPPED
IN CAPESIDE YESTERDAY.

09:56.500 --> 09:58.625
OHH! TELL ME
THEY ARE NOT ADORABLE

09:58.625 --> 10:02.250
PLUS 10 TIMES 10
TO THE 10th POWER.

10:02.250 --> 10:04.083
ANDIE, THEY
CAN HEAR YOU.
DOESN'T MATTER.

10:04.083 --> 10:05.250
ONE OF 'EM BARELY
SPEAKS ANY ENGLISH.

10:05.250 --> 10:06.500
THE OTHER ONE KNOWS
"HELLO," "GOOD-BYE,"

10:06.500 --> 10:07.750
AND THE LYRICS
TO AN 'N SYNC SONG.

10:07.750 --> 10:11.083
WE WOULD LIKE
VERY MUCH FOR YOU
TO TOUR US THE CITY.

10:11.083 --> 10:11.959
WE'D LOVE TO!

10:11.959 --> 10:14.250
UM...SORRY, BOYS.
I'M GONNA HAVE

10:14.250 --> 10:15.708
TO CATCH UP WITH YOU
ON THE RIVIERA.

10:15.708 --> 10:18.000
OK, FRENCHIES,
LET'S GO TOUR CAPESIDE

10:18.000 --> 10:20.750
AND ANY OTHER TERRAIN
YOU'RE INTERESTED IN COVERING.

10:23.500 --> 10:25.583
IT'S A FLORIDA SNOWMAN.
GET IT?

10:25.583 --> 10:28.208
NOTICE
MY FITS OF LAUGHTER.

10:28.208 --> 10:29.542
SO...OH, YEAH.

10:29.542 --> 10:32.125
HOW'S MY FAVORITE
COUCH BEEN?

10:32.125 --> 10:33.333
YOU BEEN KEEPIN' IT
WARM FOR ME?

10:33.333 --> 10:36.208
WELL, YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY
YOU SHOULD BRING THAT UP.

10:36.208 --> 10:37.625
OH, COME ON, NOW.

10:37.625 --> 10:39.458
YOU'RE
NOT GONNA CAST ME OUT
TO THE WOLVES, ARE YOU?

10:39.458 --> 10:42.291
AH, SEEMS I HAVE TO.
SOMEBODY'S ALREADY
MOVED IN. SORRY.

10:42.291 --> 10:43.458
AH.

10:43.458 --> 10:44.708
YOU AND RUPERT FINALLY
DECIDE TO TIE THE KNOT?

10:44.708 --> 10:46.708
I SEE 3 MONTHS ON THE WATER'S
DONE ABSOLUTELY NOTHING

10:46.708 --> 10:48.500
TO IMPROVE
YOUR SENSE OF HUMOR.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.750
DON'T TELL ME THIS
IS A GIRL OR SOMETHING.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.792
WELL, YES. AS A MATTER
OF FACT, IT IS.

10:51.792 --> 10:54.750
OH, WELL, THAT'S
JUST FANTASTIC.

10:54.750 --> 10:55.917
JUST AS I NEED
A PLACE TO SLEEP,

10:55.917 --> 10:56.875
YOU DECIDE TO GET
ALL HETERO ON ME.

10:56.875 --> 10:59.583
AS MUCH AS I WOULD LOVE
TO PUT AN END

10:59.583 --> 11:02.583
TO YOUR INACCURATE COMMENTS
REGARDING MY SEXUALITY,

11:02.583 --> 11:05.959
I ASSURE YOU
THAT THIS RELATIONSHIP
IS PURELY PLATONIC.

11:05.959 --> 11:08.166
GOOD. THEN I'M SURE WHOEVER
MISS MYSTERY GUEST IS

11:08.166 --> 11:11.166
COULDN'T POSSIBLY
BE AS IMPORTANT
AS YOUR BABY BRO, BRO.

11:11.166 --> 11:13.500
THAT'S WHERE
YOU'RE WRONG, 'CAUSE
SHE'S EQUALLY IMPORTANT

11:13.500 --> 11:15.208
AND...EQUALLY RELATED.

11:15.208 --> 11:18.708
SORRY I'M LATE, DOUG.
I STOPPED
AT THE HARDWARE STORE

11:18.708 --> 11:20.625
TO GET SOME LIGHT BULBS.

11:20.625 --> 11:21.834
GRETCHEN?

11:21.834 --> 11:23.667
HA HA!
NICE HAIR,
LOSER.

11:23.667 --> 11:26.208
COME GIVE
YOUR BIG SIS
A HUG.

11:26.208 --> 11:27.583
HEY.
HI.

11:51.834 --> 11:52.041
HELLO?

11:55.417 --> 11:56.625
HELLO.

11:59.375 --> 11:59.834
MRS. LEERY.

12:02.625 --> 12:02.834
MR. LEERY.

12:07.625 --> 12:07.834
DAWSON?

12:54.125 --> 12:55.250
Dawson:
SHE WAS MY FIRST CRUSH.

12:55.250 --> 12:57.333
I WAS, UH...10, 11,
SO SHE MUST'VE BEEN, WHAT,

12:57.333 --> 13:00.333
ALL OF 13?
I WAS SPENDING THE EVENING
AT THE WITTERS' HOUSE,

13:00.333 --> 13:03.708
AND GRETCHEN
AND 2 OF HER FRIENDS
WERE OUT IN THE BACKYARD.

13:03.708 --> 13:07.083
PACEY HAD THE BRILLIANT IDEA
OF WATER BALLOONING
