25:02.333 --> 25:03.834
THANKS.

25:03.834 --> 25:05.667
IT'S GOOD
TO SEE YOU.
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

25:05.667 --> 25:08.166
OH, SOMEONE'S BEEN
LIFTING THIS SUMMER.

25:08.166 --> 25:13.291
AH, YEAH.
WELL, WHAT ELSE IS THERE
TO DO IN THIS TOWN, RIGHT?

25:13.291 --> 25:15.750
SO, WHERE'D
EVERYONE GO?

25:15.750 --> 25:17.500
UH...

25:19.959 --> 25:22.000
YOU KNOW,
IT'S ONE THING
TO USURP THE COUCH,

25:22.000 --> 25:23.458
BUT IT'S QUITE ANOTHER
TO COME BACK HERE

25:23.458 --> 25:25.500
AND BEST
MY SOCIAL STANDING.

25:25.500 --> 25:26.959
DO YOU WANT
TO TAKE A WALK?

25:27.333 --> 25:29.041
YEAH.

25:31.250 --> 25:32.875
Gretchen: DO YOU HATE ME
FOR TAKING YOUR SPOT?

25:32.875 --> 25:35.125
SPOT? TRY "BED."

25:35.125 --> 25:36.125
HMM. YOU HATE ME.

25:36.125 --> 25:38.583
MARGINALLY, YEAH.

25:38.583 --> 25:40.917
WELL, RETRIBUTION
IS YOURS.

25:40.917 --> 25:44.917
DOUG WAKES ME UP
EVERY MORNING AT 7:00
DUST-BUSTERING THE KITCHEN.

25:44.917 --> 25:47.750
IT'S LIKE LIVING WITH
FELIX UNGER ON CRACK.

25:47.750 --> 25:49.959
WELL, YOU'RE
HARDLY AN INNOCENT.

25:49.959 --> 25:51.041
LAST WE ROOMED
TOGETHER,

25:51.041 --> 25:53.583
YOU WERE KNOWN
TO BLARE ROCK MUSIC
SO LOUD

25:53.583 --> 25:57.166
SMALL NATIONS
WERE KEPT UP.

25:57.166 --> 25:59.458
NOT ROCK, PACEY.
SOUL.

25:59.458 --> 26:00.375
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.

26:00.375 --> 26:01.708
YEAH, THERE
IS A DIFFERENCE.

26:01.708 --> 26:02.959
FANS LISTEN
TO ROCK MUSIC.

26:02.959 --> 26:06.834
PRETENTIOUS
FANS LISTEN
TO SOUL MUSIC.

26:06.834 --> 26:10.625
IS IT POSSIBLE
YOU'VE ACTUALLY GROWN
MORE OBNOXIOUS OVER TIME?

26:10.625 --> 26:11.625
WELL, IT IS
THE WITTER WAY.

26:11.625 --> 26:15.083
HMM. AND SOMEHOW
YOU STILL GOT THE GIRL.

26:15.083 --> 26:16.708
YES, I DID.

26:19.875 --> 26:22.125
WHO WOULD'VE EVER THUNK
ME AND JOEY WOULD
END UP TOGETHER, HUH?

26:22.125 --> 26:24.667
MMM...ME.

26:24.667 --> 26:26.000
YOU DID NOT.

26:26.000 --> 26:27.667
IT DIDN'T TAKE NOSTRADAMUS
TO CALL IT.

26:27.667 --> 26:28.625
I MEAN,
LOOK AT YOUR SIMILARITIES.

26:28.625 --> 26:32.667
YOU'RE BOTH CLASSIC
SCRAPPY UNDERDOGS.

26:32.667 --> 26:37.375
SHE'S SASSY AND YOU'RE
A LEGENDARY ANNOYANCE.

26:37.375 --> 26:43.333
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL
AND YOU'RE...LUCKY.

26:43.333 --> 26:44.750
THERE
IS A COMPLIMENT

26:44.750 --> 26:45.417
IN THERE SOMEWHERE,
RIGHT?

26:45.417 --> 26:48.041
YOU'RE BOTH LUCKY.

26:48.041 --> 26:49.333
THANK YOU.

26:51.500 --> 26:52.834
AND WHAT ABOUT YOU,
GRETCHEN?

26:52.834 --> 26:57.083
HONESTLY. WHY WOULD
YOU COME BACK HERE?

26:57.083 --> 27:01.834
I'M JUST, UH,
TAKING A BREAK.
THAT'S ALL.

27:01.834 --> 27:03.041
ALL RIGHT.

27:03.041 --> 27:05.583
WELL, AS THEY SAY
IN NON-DYSFUNCTIONAL
FAMILIES,

27:05.583 --> 27:08.417
WELCOME HOME,
GRETCHEN.

27:08.417 --> 27:11.000
AND, UH,
SPEAKING OF HOME,

27:11.000 --> 27:14.375
I HAVE A SUGGESTION
THAT I THINK YOU
MIGHT FIND APPEALING.

27:14.375 --> 27:16.125
YEAH?

27:26.792 --> 27:28.083
ASK ME A QUESTION.

27:29.875 --> 27:30.792
I GET IT.

27:30.792 --> 27:31.917
IT'S THE OLD, "LET'S
MAKE SMALL TALK

27:31.917 --> 27:32.875
UNTIL HE
COMES OVER," RIGHT?

27:32.875 --> 27:36.458
PRECISELY.
JUST ASK ME A QUESTION.

27:36.458 --> 27:38.834
ACTUALLY, I DO
HAVE A QUESTION.

27:41.291 --> 27:41.959
NOT THAT  QUESTION.

27:41.959 --> 27:42.792
COME ON!
JACK!

27:42.792 --> 27:45.166
I WON'T TELL
ANYBODY. I SWEAR.

27:45.166 --> 27:47.708
SHE'S DOING THE OFFICIAL
"WAIT FOR DAWSON
TO COME OVER" THING.

27:47.708 --> 27:49.917
IT LOOKS TO ME
MORE LIKE THE OFFICIAL

27:49.917 --> 27:52.625
"WAIT IN VAIN FOR DAWSON
TO COME OVER" THING.

27:54.458 --> 27:55.625
ONE MORE JOKE LIKE THAT
AND I AM REALLY
GOING TO KNOW

27:55.625 --> 27:57.583
HOW HARD
THIS IS FOR YOU.

27:57.583 --> 28:00.000
IT'S NOT HARD.
COME ON.

28:00.000 --> 28:02.417
IT'S NOT. IT'S NOT EASY,
BUT IT'S NOT HARD.

28:02.417 --> 28:04.333
WELL, WHATEVER IT IS,
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GO GET IT OVER WITH?

28:04.333 --> 28:07.667
I'LL DO IT,
BUT IT'S JUST A HIGHLY
PREDICTABLE MOMENT.

28:07.667 --> 28:09.000
I'M GOING
TO WALK OVER THERE,

28:09.000 --> 28:12.417
JOEY AND I
ARE GONNA ENGAGE IN SOME
SEMI-CASUAL CONVERSATION

28:12.417 --> 28:14.417
UNTIL THE AWKWARDNESS
OVERWHELMS US BOTH,

28:14.417 --> 28:16.166
AND THEN
WE'RE JUST GONNA PART...

28:17.667 --> 28:18.834
EACH OF US
SURPRISED AT HOW
SURPRISINGLY PAINLESS

28:18.834 --> 28:22.417
THE WHOLE ENCOUNTER
SURPRISINGLY WAS.

28:22.417 --> 28:24.875
WELL THEN, SURPRISE ME
AND GO ON OVER THERE.

28:27.500 --> 28:28.834
ALL RIGHT.

28:35.083 --> 28:36.375
HEY.

28:36.375 --> 28:37.834
HEY.

28:42.208 --> 28:44.417
YEAH. I'M GONNA
GO FIND JEN.

28:44.417 --> 28:46.875
SHE'S RIGHT OVER THERE.
OK. THANKS.

28:51.166 --> 28:52.500
SO, HOW'S IT GOING?

28:52.500 --> 28:55.208
UH, GREAT. GREAT.
IT'S GOING GREAT.

28:56.792 --> 28:57.834
Joey:
HOW WAS YOUR SUMMER?

28:57.834 --> 28:59.917
UH, IT WAS BRIEF
BUT GOOD.

29:02.875 --> 29:05.166
YOURS?

29:05.166 --> 29:08.125
BRIEF BUT GOOD.

29:08.125 --> 29:09.917
YOU LOOK GREAT.

29:09.917 --> 29:10.542
HEY, YOU, TOO.

29:10.542 --> 29:12.250
THANKS.
YOU, TOO.

29:12.250 --> 29:15.041
THANKS.

29:25.500 --> 29:27.750
SO, UH...

29:27.750 --> 29:29.708
SCHOOL'S MONDAY--
SCHOOL'S IN--

29:29.708 --> 29:29.917
YEAH.

29:38.959 --> 29:39.959
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

29:43.917 --> 29:45.500
IT'S GOOD
TO SEE YOU, TOO.

30:12.792 --> 30:15.792
OH, UH, HOLD ON
A MINUTE, GUYS.

30:15.792 --> 30:19.166
THERE'S SOMEONE
THAT I'M NOT QUITE
READY TO SEE YET.

30:21.834 --> 30:24.375
UH...
HOW DO YOU SAY

30:24.375 --> 30:27.375
EX-BOYFRIEND?

30:27.375 --> 30:29.417
I UNDERSTAND.

30:30.834 --> 30:34.041
SO DO YOU HAPPEN
TO BE IN A, UM...

30:34.041 --> 30:36.041
HER NAME IS NICOLE.

30:36.041 --> 30:38.375
AND I BET YOU'RE
CRAZY ABOUT HER,
AREN'T YOU?

30:38.375 --> 30:39.542
TO BORROW YOUR WORDS,

30:39.542 --> 30:41.667
SHE'S MONET,
DEGAS, CÃ©ZANNE--

30:41.667 --> 30:44.583
OK, I GET THE POINT.

30:47.750 --> 30:49.000
OF COURSE
HE HAS A GIRLFRIEND.

30:49.000 --> 30:52.333
HE'S CUTE.
HE HAS AN ACCENT,

30:52.333 --> 30:53.750
AND HE TELLS ME
THAT I'M BEAUTIFUL,

30:53.750 --> 30:55.166
SO OF COURSE HE HAS
A GIRLFRIEND, RIGHT?

30:55.166 --> 30:56.458
I MEAN, YOU GUYS
ARE ALL THE SAME.

30:56.458 --> 30:58.500
IT DOESN'T MATTER
IF YOU'RE FRENCH,
AMERICAN, ENGLISH,

30:58.500 --> 31:00.625
GERMAN, RUSSIAN,
DUTCH, FRENCH.

31:00.625 --> 31:03.083
WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING AT?

31:03.083 --> 31:04.625
A VERY RUDE GIRL.

31:04.625 --> 31:06.708
OK, YOU DON'T
EVEN KNOW ME, SO--

31:07.917 --> 31:11.208
UH...
YOU DON'T SPEAK ENGLISH.

31:11.208 --> 31:13.583
I HAVE IT ON GOOD AUTHORITY
THAT I DO.

31:13.583 --> 31:15.375
OK, BUT YOU GUYS
TOLD ME--

31:15.375 --> 31:17.083
IT WAS A JOKE.

31:17.083 --> 31:18.667
THE NAME'S J.J.

31:18.667 --> 31:21.375
SHORT FOR JOHN-JOHN,
NOT JEAN-JEAN.

31:21.375 --> 31:24.208
SO THAT MEANS
THAT ALL DAY YOU--

31:24.208 --> 31:26.208
UNDERSTOOD
EVERY WORD YOU SAID.

31:28.083 --> 31:31.083
PARDON MOI.
I'M JUST GONNA
GO DROWN MYSELF.

31:42.417 --> 31:44.417
THERE YOU ARE.

31:44.417 --> 31:46.291
AND HERE WE GO.

31:46.291 --> 31:47.708
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:47.708 --> 31:49.875
BOTH OF US A FAVOR.
TAKING US HOME.

31:49.875 --> 31:52.291
YOU DON'T EVEN ASK ME
IF I WANT TO GO?

31:52.291 --> 31:54.208
DO I HAVE TO?

31:54.208 --> 31:57.542
MAYBE I'M
HAVING A FUN TIME.

31:57.542 --> 31:59.917
IF THIS IS HOW
YOU LOOK WHEN YOU'RE
ENJOYING YOURSELF, JO,

31:59.917 --> 32:02.000
THEN YOU WEREN'T
HAVING A VERY GOOD TIME
ON THE BOAT THIS SUMMER,

32:02.000 --> 32:03.083
'CAUSE YOU NEVER ONCE
LOOKED LIKE THIS.

32:03.083 --> 32:06.250
AND YOU NEVER ONCE
BEHAVED LIKE THIS.

32:06.250 --> 32:07.959
AND JUST
HOW AM I BEHAVING?

32:07.959 --> 32:10.125
I DON'T KNOW YET.
CURRENTLY I'M DECIDING

32:10.125 --> 32:12.083
BETWEEN ASININE,
IMMATURE CHILD

32:12.083 --> 32:15.000
AND ARROGANT,
INFANTILE BOYFRIEND.

32:15.000 --> 32:16.875
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T
WANT TO COME HERE
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

32:16.875 --> 32:18.417
WELL, THEN,
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE COME.

32:21.083 --> 32:24.375
YEAH. I GUESS YOU WOULD
HAVE LOVED THAT, HUH?

32:24.375 --> 32:25.834
WOULD HAVE GIVEN YOU
ALL THE TIME
IN THE WORLD

32:25.834 --> 32:27.625
TO SQUARE THINGS AWAY
WITH DAWSON.

32:27.625 --> 32:29.083
THOSE WERE
YOUR WORDS, RIGHT?
"SQUARE THINGS AWAY"?

32:29.083 --> 32:31.792
PACEY, DEALING WITH DAWSON
IS A REALITY FOR ME.

32:31.792 --> 32:33.083
IT'S A REALITY
FOR THE BOTH OF US.

32:33.083 --> 32:34.000
THE GUY HATES ME, OK?
I CAN'T FIX THAT.

32:34.000 --> 32:36.875
WELL, YOU COULD TRY.
I DON'T WANT TO!

32:36.875 --> 32:39.708
WELL, I DO,
AND I'M SORRY IF YOU
HAVE A PROBLEM WITH THAT!

32:39.708 --> 32:41.458
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT I HAVE
A PROBLEM WITH THAT!

32:41.458 --> 32:43.583
YOU'RE NOT EVEN UNPACKED
YET AND THE FIRST THINK
YOU THINK TO DO IS--

32:43.583 --> 32:45.208
LOOK I CAN'T HELP IT
IF HE'S BEEN ON MY MIND,

32:45.208 --> 32:46.458
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
WHAT YOU THINK IT MEANS.

32:46.458 --> 32:48.417
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT MEANS.
I DON'T CARE WHAT IT MEANS.

32:48.417 --> 32:50.000
I'VE JUST WATCHED YOU GROW
MORE AND MORE PREOCCUPIED

32:50.000 --> 32:52.708
EVERY DAY THIS WEEK,
AND I'M TIRED OF IT.

32:52.708 --> 32:54.792
AND IT BETTER STOP.

32:54.792 --> 32:57.750
YOU BETTER WATCH WHO
YOU'RE ORDERING AROUND, PACEY.

32:57.750 --> 32:59.792
WE'RE NOT ON THE BOAT
AND WE HAVEN'T BEEN FOR A DAY.

32:59.792 --> 33:01.625
WHO ARE YOU KIDDING, JO?

33:01.625 --> 33:05.834
COME ON. YOU GOT OFF
THAT BOAT LONG BEFORE
THE TWO OF US DID.

33:05.834 --> 33:07.708
WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

33:07.708 --> 33:10.792
YOU'RE A SMART GIRL, JO.
YOU CAN FIGURE IT OUT.

33:28.417 --> 33:30.083
STILL HERE, HUH?

33:32.166 --> 33:33.542
YEAH.
I WAS JUST THINKING.

33:33.542 --> 33:36.250
A HIGHLY OVERRATED ACTIVITY,
IF YOU ASK ME.

33:39.166 --> 33:40.291
SO, ARE YOU
HEADING HOME?

33:40.291 --> 33:42.250
YEAH.

33:42.250 --> 33:43.458
DO YOU NEED A RIDE?

33:44.959 --> 33:47.667
I WOULD LIKE THAT,
DAWSON.

33:50.083 --> 33:54.041
ANDIE, YOU WERE
A WONDERFUL HOST.

33:54.041 --> 33:55.959
IF YOU COME TO PARIS,
YOU MUST LOOK ME UP.

33:55.959 --> 33:59.333
OK. YOU HAVE A DEAL,
JEAN.

33:59.333 --> 34:01.708
EXCUSEZ-MOI.

34:05.208 --> 34:07.959
THAT, UM, GOES FOR ME,
TOO, YOU KNOW.

34:07.959 --> 34:09.166
[LAUGHS]

34:09.166 --> 34:11.625
I CAN'T BELIEVE
AFTER EVERYTHING
YOU HEARD ME SAY

34:11.625 --> 34:13.208
THAT YOU'D STILL
WANT TO HANG OUT
WITH ME.

34:13.208 --> 34:15.208
ME EITHER.

34:15.208 --> 34:18.833
OK, I THINK
I LIKED YOU BETTER
BEFORE YOU SPOKE ENGLISH.

34:21.500 --> 34:24.458
THERE'S A QUESTION IN FRENCH.
IT'S VERY POPULAR.

34:24.458 --> 34:27.208
THE ENGLISH TRANSLATION,
IF I CAN REMEMBER CORRECTLY,

34:27.208 --> 34:29.083
GOES SOMETHING LIKE THIS:

34:29.083 --> 34:31.500
CAN I KISS YOU?

34:34.250 --> 34:35.291
OUI.

34:47.041 --> 34:51.083
SO, TELL ME ABOUT
THIS NEWLY ACQUIRED
LOVE OF PHOTOGRAPHY

34:51.083 --> 34:53.625
THAT SEEMS TO HAVE
SPRUNG UP IN MY ABSENCE.

34:53.625 --> 34:56.417
UH, I PICKED IT UP
OVER THE SUMMER.

34:56.417 --> 34:57.667
DIDN'T THINK
I'D LIKE IT

34:57.667 --> 34:58.166
NEARLY AS MUCH
AS I HAVE,

34:58.166 --> 35:00.417
BUT, YOU KNOW,

35:00.417 --> 35:01.792
I GUESS
THAT'S THE WAY
IT ALWAYS IS, HUH?

35:01.792 --> 35:03.125
WHAT'S THAT?

35:03.125 --> 35:05.208
YOU DON'T CHOOSE
WHAT YOU LOVE,
IT CHOOSES YOU.

35:11.458 --> 35:13.000
DAWSON, UH...

35:15.792 --> 35:19.458
I'M VERY SORRY.

35:19.458 --> 35:23.542
I'M SORRY FOR EVERYTHING
THAT HAPPENED LAST YEAR

35:23.542 --> 35:29.708
AND FOR DOING
WHAT I HAD TO DO.

35:29.708 --> 35:34.583
I KNOW HOW DIFFICULT IT WAS
AND PROBABLY STILL MUST BE.

35:37.250 --> 35:39.959
IT WASN'T EASY...

35:39.959 --> 35:42.917
THINKING ABOUT
THE TWO OF YOU TOGETHER
EVERY DAY, EVERY NIGHT.

35:47.166 --> 35:48.583
YOU'RE ACTUALLY
THE ONLY PERSON

35:48.583 --> 35:52.875
WHO HASN'T DARED
ASK THE BIG QUESTION.

35:52.875 --> 35:55.834
I'M THE ONLY PERSON
THE ANSWER COULD
POTENTIALLY KILL.

35:56.792 --> 35:59.208
WAIT HERE.

36:06.125 --> 36:07.333
IT'S FOR YOU.

36:09.041 --> 36:10.250
OK.

36:13.500 --> 36:16.291
WOW.
IT'S MY VERY OWN BRICK.

36:16.291 --> 36:17.291
IT'S NOT JUST A BRICK.

36:17.291 --> 36:19.417
IT'S FROM HEMINGWAY'S
HOME IN THE KEYS.

36:21.750 --> 36:22.875
ERNEST?

36:22.875 --> 36:24.583
NO. FRANK.
OF COURSE ERNEST.

36:25.500 --> 36:27.750
YOU KNOW THE GUY
SHOT HIMSELF, JO.

36:27.750 --> 36:28.708
ASIDE FROM THAT,

36:28.708 --> 36:32.000
I WOULD LIKE TO OFFER IT
TO YOU AS A--

36:32.000 --> 36:34.625
PLEASE DON'T SAY
"SYMBOL."

36:34.625 --> 36:38.417
AS AN EMBLEMATIC ARTIFACT

36:38.417 --> 36:42.500
REPRESENTING
THE FOUNDATION OF--

36:42.500 --> 36:44.875
OF A NEW FRIENDSHIP.

36:44.875 --> 36:46.875
I FEEL LIKE
I'M AT THE RIBBON-CUTTING
OF A NEW STRIP MALL.

36:46.875 --> 36:50.000
QUIT JOKING.

36:50.000 --> 36:52.166
TRUTH IS, JOEY...

36:52.166 --> 36:54.166
IT'S GONNA TAKE
A HELL OF A LOT
MORE THAN SYMBOLS

36:54.166 --> 36:55.375
FOR US TO GET BACK
WHAT WE HAD,

36:55.375 --> 36:57.834
AND RIGHT NOW
I'M NOT EVEN SURE
THAT I WANT TO.

37:03.875 --> 37:07.041
WE'RE JUST GONNA
HAVE TO TAKE IT
ONE DAY AT A TIME.

37:09.000 --> 37:10.208
I KNOW.

37:28.583 --> 37:29.834
HEY, DAWSON.
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

37:29.834 --> 37:35.125
THE ANSWER TO THAT
QUESTION EVERYONE'S
BEEN ASKING?

37:35.125 --> 37:37.542
IT WOULDN'T
KILL YOU.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.250
[CLEARS THROAT]

38:13.917 --> 38:15.417
WELL,
I'VE DECIDED SOMETHING,

38:15.417 --> 38:18.125
AND IT IS PERHAPS
THE SINGULARLY
MOST IMPORTANT THING

38:18.125 --> 38:19.959
THAT I'VE REALIZED
IN THE LAST 45 MINUTES,

38:19.959 --> 38:21.333
SO I MUST SHARE IT
WITH YOU.

38:21.333 --> 38:24.083
THIS TOWN HAS
FAR TOO MANY STOPLIGHTS

38:24.083 --> 38:26.542
FOR SOMEBODY
WHO'S NOT VERY GOOD
AT DRIVING STICK.

38:26.542 --> 38:28.667
I STALLED 7 TIMES
COMING OVER HERE.

38:30.959 --> 38:32.375
TOO BAD IT WASN'T 8.

38:36.542 --> 38:42.041
I STALLED 7 TIMES
AND 6 OUT OF THE 7 TIMES,

38:42.041 --> 38:42.417
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I THOUGHT ABOUT?

38:44.750 --> 38:46.667
YOU.

38:49.542 --> 38:53.625
IT'S THIS SECRET THING I DO
WHENEVER I GET REALLY PISSED OFF

38:53.625 --> 38:56.041
OR CONFUSED OR ANGRY

38:56.041 --> 38:58.834
OR UPSET OR SAD.

38:58.834 --> 39:04.458
I--I THINK OF YOU, AND I
IMMEDIATELY FEEL GOOD INSIDE.

39:04.458 --> 39:07.667
I GUESS
IT'S KIND OF LIKE TAKING
A GOOD MOOD PILL OR SOMETHING.

39:10.917 --> 39:13.625
AND I SWORE TO MYSELF
THAT I WOULD NEVER TELL YOU
THAT I DID THIS,

39:13.625 --> 39:15.708
BECAUSE IT IS
SO GIRLY AND STUPID,

39:15.708 --> 39:19.875
AND I JUST TOLD YOU
BECAUSE...

39:19.875 --> 39:20.875
I NEEDED TO SCORE
MAJOR POINTS

39:20.875 --> 39:25.333
FOR NOT EXPLAINING
WHAT WENT DOWN TONIGHT

39:25.333 --> 39:27.250
OR WHERE I'VE BEEN
THE LAST WEEK

39:27.250 --> 39:28.875
WHEN I HAVEN'T BEEN
ON THIS BOAT.

39:32.667 --> 39:33.667
KEEP GOING.

39:36.583 --> 39:37.542
PACEY...

39:42.375 --> 39:43.917
I WANTED
TO SEE DAWSON TONIGHT

39:43.917 --> 39:47.291
NOT BECAUSE
FOR 4 MONTHS OF MY LIFE
HE WAS MY BOYFRIEND,

39:47.291 --> 39:51.041
BUT BECAUSE FOR
THE BETTER PART OF MY LIFE
HE WAS MY FRIEND.

39:51.041 --> 39:53.500
AND AS MY FRIEND,
I HURT HIM DEEPLY.

39:53.500 --> 39:56.542
LIVING WITH THAT FACT
HAS CAUSED ME

39:56.542 --> 39:59.667
NO SMALL AMOUNT OF GUILT
OVER THE PAST 3 MONTHS.

39:59.667 --> 40:03.375
SO, YES,
I HAVE BEEN PREOCCUPIED,

40:03.375 --> 40:07.166
AND IT HAS
MADE MY MIND WANDER.

40:07.166 --> 40:08.417
BUT...

40:11.208 --> 40:12.417
MY HEART?

40:17.500 --> 40:18.583
THAT'S A FIXED POINT.

40:21.875 --> 40:26.041
3 MONTHS
RIDING THE OPEN WATERS
COULDN'T SHAKE IT,

40:26.041 --> 40:28.583
AND I'LL BE DAMNED
IF I'LL LET YOUR
INSECURITIES SHAKE IT.

40:33.500 --> 40:35.583
MY HEART
NEVER LEFT THIS BOAT.

40:37.083 --> 40:39.583
IT'S NEVER LEFT YOU.

40:41.083 --> 40:44.625
AS FAR AS I CAN SEE,
IT'S NOT GOING TO
ANY TIME SOON.

40:47.000 --> 40:48.708
OK, YOU GOT ME.

40:50.750 --> 40:52.375
I DO WANT TO KNOW
ONE THING, THOUGH.

40:54.667 --> 40:55.166
WHAT'S THAT?

40:55.166 --> 40:57.667
I WANT TO KNOW

40:57.667 --> 40:59.375
WHAT EXACTLY IT WAS
YOU THOUGHT OF

40:59.375 --> 41:02.708
THE SEVENTH TIME
YOU STALLED.

41:02.708 --> 41:05.291
THAT I WAS NEVER
GOING TO DRIVE
STICK AGAIN.

41:06.792 --> 41:08.500
HOW VERY PRACTICAL.

41:19.959 --> 41:22.333
HEY, PACE?

41:22.333 --> 41:23.542
HMM?

41:25.625 --> 41:28.583
DO YOU THINK
WE COULD DO THAT THING
THAT WE DO SOMETIMES?

41:31.417 --> 41:33.875
YOU WANNA
DO THAT THING?

41:37.542 --> 41:37.750
YEAH.

41:44.625 --> 41:47.166
Joey: "THE LITTLE MERMAID
COULD NOT TAKE HER EYES
FROM THE SHIP

41:47.166 --> 41:49.333
"OR FROM
THE BEAUTIFUL PRINCE.

41:49.333 --> 41:51.125
"THE COLORED LANTERNS
HAD BEEN EXTINGUISHED.

41:51.125 --> 41:52.834
"NO MORE ROCKETS
ROSE IN THE AIR

41:52.834 --> 41:54.500
"AND THE CANNON
HAD CEASED FIRING.

41:54.500 --> 41:55.458
"BUT THE SEA
BECAME RESTLESS

41:55.458 --> 41:56.542
"AND A MOANING,
GRUMBLING SOUND

41:56.542 --> 41:59.208
COULD BE HEARD
BENEATH THE WAVES."

42:06.667 --> 42:10.208
"AFTER AWHILE, THE SAILS
WERE QUICKLY UNFURLED,

42:10.208 --> 42:12.458
"AND THE NOBLE SHIP
CONTINUED HER PASSAGE,

42:12.458 --> 42:15.375
"BUT SOON THE WAVES
ROSE HIGHER.

42:15.375 --> 42:17.083
"HEAVY CLOUDS
DARKENED THE SKY

42:17.083 --> 42:19.208
"AND LIGHTNING
APPEARED IN THE DISTANCE.

42:19.208 --> 42:21.417
"A DREADFUL STORM
WAS APPROACHING.

42:21.417 --> 42:23.250
"ONCE MORE THE SAILS
WERE REEFED

42:23.250 --> 42:27.208
"AND THE GREAT SHIP
PURSUED HER FLYING COURSE
OVER THE RAGING SEA.

42:27.208 --> 42:30.250
"TO THE LITTLE MERMAID,
THIS APPEARED
PLEASANT SPORT.

42:30.250 --> 42:31.250
NOT SO FOR THE SAILORS."
